==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heteropelmous
<hw>Het`er*o*pel"mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hetero-</ets> + Gr. <?/ the sole of the foot.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having each of the two flexor tendons of the
toes bifid, the branches of one going to the first and second toes;
those of the other, to the third and fourth toes. See <xex>Illust.</xex>
in Append.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heterophagi</ent>⟦br⟧
